# Velocity — Final QA Checklist

**How to use this:** Go top to bottom, in order. Don't skip around — earlier sections (deployment, auth) being broken makes everything below untestable. For each item: do the exact action listed, confirm the exact expected result, check the box. If it fails, note it and keep going — don't stop to fix mid-pass, finish the full pass first so you know your complete list of real bugs before you start fixing anything.

Test on the **live deployed URL**, not localhost, unless explicitly noted. Things that work locally can break in production (cold starts, env vars, CORS, OAuth redirect URIs) — this checklist exists specifically to catch those.

---

## 0. DEPLOYMENT & INFRASTRUCTURE (test this first — nothing else matters if this fails)

- [ ] **Live URL loads** — open the deployed link in an incognito/private window (no cached login, no saved state). Page loads within ~5 seconds. No blank white screen, no console errors visible on first paint.
- [ ] **Cold start latency check** — if the app hasn't been hit in a while, the *first* request to your Cloud Run backend may take a few extra seconds (cold start). Test this deliberately: wait 10+ minutes without touching the app, then load it. If it hangs unacceptably long, consider setting a minimum instance count on Cloud Run so it never fully cold-starts during the judging window.
- [ ] **No localhost references leaked** — open browser dev tools → Network tab, click around the app, confirm every API call goes to your actual deployed backend URL, not `localhost:3000` or similar. A single leaked localhost call will silently fail in production.
- [ ] **HTTPS, not HTTP** — confirm the URL is `https://`, padlock icon shows valid, no mixed-content warnings in console.
- [ ] **CORS works** — no CORS errors in console when frontend calls backend. If you see red CORS errors, your `ALLOWED_ORIGIN` env var on the backend doesn't match your actual frontend URL.
- [ ] **Refreshing any page works** (not just the homepage) — navigate to a deep route (e.g., Activity Log, Command Day), hit browser refresh. Should reload that same page, not 404. (This is the SPA rewrite-rule check for Firebase Hosting.)
- [ ] **Health check endpoint responds** — manually visit `https://your-backend-url/api/health` in a browser tab. Should return `200 OK` / a simple JSON response, not an error.

