## 2. CORE TASK MANAGEMENT

- [ ] **Brain Dump Engine** — paste a messy block of text with 3-4 implied tasks and deadlines. Confirm Gemini extracts structured tasks with reasonable deadlines/priorities, not garbage or empty output.
- [ ] **Chaos Scanner** — upload a photo of a whiteboard/syllabus (use a real test image, not a blank one). Confirm it actually reads tasks out of the image via Gemini Vision, not just OCRs raw text without structuring it.
- [ ] **Manual task creation** — create a task by hand (if a manual "add task" path exists separately from Brain Dump). Confirm it appears immediately in the task list.
- [ ] **Drag-to-Reorder** — grab a task card by its grip handle, drag it to a new position. Confirm the order actually persists after a page refresh (not just visually reordered until reload).
- [ ] **Task check-in / progress update** — manually update a task's progress percentage. Confirm it saves and reflects on the card immediately.
- [ ] **Task completion** — mark a task complete. Confirm it moves to a completed state/list and isn't still showing as active.

