## 4. BEHAVIORAL VELOCITY SYSTEM (Drift Score / Deadline Physics / Trust Decay / Velocity Vector)

This is your centerpiece — test it harder than anything else.

- [ ] **Drift Score shows on at least one seeded task** with a meaningful, clearly-explained gap (e.g., "Reported: 60% · Real estimate: 35%").
- [ ] **Drift Score "Why?" expansion works** — tapping it reveals the actual contributing signals (Panic Mode usage, staleness, subtask ratio) in plain English, not a generic/blank explanation.
- [ ] **ADVERSARIAL TEST — sparse data graceful degradation**: create a brand-new task with zero check-ins, zero subtasks ticked, no Panic Mode history. Confirm the Drift Score does **NOT** show an aggressive/confident "you're lying" message — it should show a neutral "not enough activity to estimate" state instead. **This is the single highest-risk failure mode in the entire app — test it explicitly, don't assume it works.**
- [ ] **ADVERSARIAL TEST — false positive check**: take a task, report an honest, low percentage, and check in frequently. Confirm Drift Score does NOT falsely flag a gap when behavior actually matches the claim.
- [ ] **Deadline Physics curve renders and visibly steepens** — compare a task due in 7 days vs. a task due in 1-2 days side by side. The near-deadline task's card should visually read as more urgent (curve, color, animation) without you reading any numbers.
- [ ] **Trust Decay bar actually drains over time** — find or seed a task with no check-in in 24-48h. Confirm its progress bar shows a visibly different (lower/adjusted) value than what was last self-reported, with a label explaining why ("Last reported X ago — showing adjusted estimate").
- [ ] **Trust Decay resets on check-in** — check in on a decayed task, confirm the bar immediately resets to the fresh reported value and the decay halts.
- [ ] **Velocity Vector renders in the header/Command Day** and is NOT just a static icon — confirm it visually reflects current state (direction/magnitude) and isn't identical regardless of underlying data.
- [ ] **Velocity Vector deep-link works** — clicking it takes you to a view explaining which tasks are dragging the vector in which direction.
- [ ] **Drift Score logs to Activity Log** — confirm a significant detected drift (>25% gap) produces a real entry in the Activity Log, not just a UI-only notification that disappears.

