## 8. ADAPTIVE POLICY MEMORY

- [ ] **Three cancellations trigger a policy change** — cancel the same category of autonomous action 3 times in a row (e.g., cancel 3 Negotiate auto-sends to the same context). Confirm the 4th time, the agent does NOT auto-act, and instead flags a suggestion only.
- [ ] **Agent Memory tab exists and is reachable** from the Activity Log page.
- [ ] **Agent Memory tab shows learned behaviors in plain English** — e.g., "Learned: no longer auto-sending Negotiate emails to [type] based on your past overrides."
- [ ] **Cancel-count progress bars display correctly** for policies still being tracked (e.g., "2 of 3 cancellations — one more and I'll stop auto-acting here").
- [ ] **Seeded demo account shows at least 2 pre-existing learned behaviors** on first login, without you having to trigger the 3-cancellation threshold yourself.

